<strong>The Most Effective Home Remedies Lose 10 kg weight in just one month</strong>

Whenever it comes to weight loss, First of all, dieting and workout are advised, Dieting is not so easy But still, some people lose weight by dieting, But it is not possible to have a diet for a long time and Lose 10 kg weight just one month.

That is why we have brought for you, three such drinks which you can reduce weight up to ten kilos in a month very easily, at the same time you will see the difference between stomach fat three to four inches in the first ten days, its results are so good.
Those people who have diabetes, thyroid also can use it, with these drinks, our body gets less fat in a day as well as in the night, For this reason, we get miraculous results from this drink.

<strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">Women who are pregnant, women menstrual periods, and baby lactation, do not have to consume these drinks.</span></strong>

<strong><span style="color: #008000;">We need all these things to make the first drink -</span></strong>

Curry Leaves ( kadi patta)
Ginger (adrak)
Cardamom (Elaichi)
Coriander (Dhaniya)
Fennel Seeds (Souff)
Amla/Awla
Cinnamon (Daalchini)
Garlic(Lahsun)

<strong><span style="color: #008000;">To Make </span></strong>It:<strong><span style="color: #008000;">-</span></strong>
1. Add one to one and a half glass of water in a vessel, let it warm on a high flame,
2.When the water starts to boil well, then first pour two cardamoms together with peels,
3. Add half a teaspoon finely chopped ginger,
4. Put a teaspoon Fennel Seeds (Souff),
5. Put about ten to fifteen Curry Leaves ( kadi patta),
6. Put a bowl chopped coriander with root,
7. Put two teaspoons of chopped garlic,
8. Put half teaspoon cinnamon powder,
9. Put a well-chopped amla, if not available amla powder can be use.
10. Reduce flame and let it boil for two to three minutes,
11. Cool it and filter it well,
12. Prepare a paste with the help of mixer of all the boiled things,
13.In the prepared paste, mix well the remaining water in which everything was boiled,
